Evaluate Batting Performance:

If runs ≥ 50 and strike rate ≥ 120 → Excellent Batter

Else if runs ≥ 30 and strike rate ≥ 100 → Good Batter

Else if runs ≥ 20 → Average Batter

Else → Poor Batter

Evaluate Bowling Performance:

If wickets ≥ 3 and economy ≤ 6 → Excellent Bowler

Else if wickets ≥ 2 and economy ≤ 8 → Good Bowler

Else if wickets ≥ 1 → Average Bowler

Else → Poor Bowler

Evaluate Fielding Performance:

If catches ≥ 2 → Outstanding Fielder

Else if catches = 1 → Active Fielder

Else → Needs Improvement

Determine Overall All-Rounder Performance:

If batter is Excellent and bowler is Excellent → Star All-Rounder

Else if batter is Good and bowler is Good → Strong All-Rounder

Else if batter is Good or bowler is Good → Supporting All-Rounder

Else → Needs Improvement

